    FUNCTION multiply(num1 string num2 string) RETURNS string  
        IF num1 EQUALS string zero OR num2 EQUALS string zero  
            RETURN string zero  
        END IF

        SET num2 TO the reversal of num2

                SET p2 TO i PLUS j PLUS one  
                SET sum TO mul PLUS the element at position p1 of result

                INCREMENT the element at position p2 of result BY the integer division of sum BY ten  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  

        SET result_str TO the concatenation of the string representations of the elements of result in reverse order

    END FUNCTION

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION diffWaysToCompute(expression)  
        FUNCTION compute(left, right, operator)  
            SET results TO an empty list  
            FOR each l IN left  
                FOR each r IN right  
                    IF operator EQUALS the plus symbol  
                        APPEND l PLUS r TO results  
                    ELSE IF operator EQUALS the minus symbol  
                        APPEND l MINUS r TO results  
                    ELSE IF operator EQUALS the multiplication symbol  
                        APPEND l MULTIPLIED BY r TO results  
                    END IF  
                END FOR  
            END FOR  
            RETURN results  
        END FUNCTION  
      
        FUNCTION helper(sub_expr)  
            IF the entirety of sub_expr CONSISTS OF DIGITS  
                RETURN a list containing the integer value of sub_expr  
            END IF  
          
            SET results TO an empty list  
            FOR index i FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF sub_expr MINUS one  
                IF the element at position i of sub_expr EQUALS any of the plus symbol OR the minus symbol OR the multiplication symbol  
                    SET left_results TO helper(the substring of sub_expr from position zero TO position i MINUS one)  
                    SET right_results TO helper(the substring of sub_expr from position i PLUS one TO the last position)  
                    FOR each result IN compute(left_results, right_results, the element at position i of sub_expr)  
                        APPEND result TO results  
                    END FOR  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
            RETURN results  
        END FUNCTION  
      
        RETURN helper(expression)  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION wordSquares(words)  
        SET prefix_to_words TO an empty mapping from string to list of strings  
        FOR each word IN words  
            FOR index FROM zero TO the LENGTH OF word MINUS one  
                SET prefix TO the substring of word from position zero TO position index MINUS one  
                APPEND word TO the list at prefix_to_words corresponding to prefix  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        SET results TO an empty list  
        
        FUNCTION backtrack(square)  
            IF the LENGTH OF square EQUALS the LENGTH OF the first element of words THEN  
                APPEND square TO results  
                RETURN  
            END IF  
            
            SET prefix TO an empty string  
            FOR each word_element IN square  
                APPEND the element at position the LENGTH OF square of word_element TO prefix  
            END FOR  
            
            FOR each candidate IN the list at prefix_to_words corresponding to prefix  
                CALL backtrack WITH the argument of the concatenation of square with candidate as a new list element  
            END FOR  
        END FUNCTION  
        
        FOR each word IN words  
            CALL backtrack WITH a list containing only word  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN results  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION medianSlidingWindow(nums k)  
        SET lo TO empty list  
        SET hi TO empty list  

        FUNCTION balance_heaps()  
            IF the LENGTH OF lo IS GREATER THAN the LENGTH OF hi PLUS one  
                CALL heappush WITH the argument hi AND NEGATIVE of the result of heappop ON lo  
            ELSE IF the LENGTH OF hi IS GREATER THAN the LENGTH OF lo  
                CALL heappush WITH the argument lo AND NEGATIVE of the result of heappop ON hi  
            END IF  
        END FUNCTION  

        FUNCTION add_num(num)  
            IF lo IS empty OR num IS LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO NEGATIVE of element at position zero of lo  
                CALL heappush WITH the argument lo AND NEGATIVE num  
            ELSE  
                CALL heappush WITH the argument hi AND num  
            END IF  
            CALL balance_heaps()  
        END FUNCTION  

        FUNCTION remove_num(num)  
            IF num IS LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO NEGATIVE of element at position zero of lo  
                REMOVE NEGATIVE num FROM lo  
                IF lo IS NOT empty  
                    CALL heapify WITH the argument lo  
                END IF  
            ELSE  
                REMOVE num FROM hi  
                IF hi IS NOT empty  
                    CALL heapify WITH the argument hi  
                END IF  
            END IF  
            CALL balance_heaps()  
        END FUNCTION  

        FUNCTION get_median()  
            IF the LENGTH OF lo IS GREATER THAN the LENGTH OF hi  
                RETURN NEGATIVE of element at position zero of lo  
            END IF  
            RETURN NEGATIVE of element at position zero of lo PLUS element at position zero of hi DIVIDED BY two  
        END FUNCTION  

        FOR i FROM zero TO k MINUS one  
            CALL add_num WITH element at position i of nums  
        END FOR  

        SET medians TO a list containing the result of get_median()  

        FOR i FROM k TO the LENGTH OF nums MINUS one  
            CALL add_num WITH element at position i of nums  
            CALL remove_num WITH element at position i MINUS k of nums  
            APPEND the result of get_median() TO medians  
        END FOR  

        RETURN medians  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

            SET numeric_value TO integer VALUE OF n

        END IF

        FOR i FROM negative one TO positive one  
            SET new_prefix_numeric TO prefix PLUS i  
            SET new_prefix TO string REPRESENTATION OF new_prefix_numeric  
            
            IF length MODULO two EQUALS zero  
                SET reversed_part TO the REVERSED STRING OF new_prefix

                SET smallest_distance TO current_distance

        END FOR  
        
        RETURN string REPRESENTATION OF closest  
    END FUNCTION

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION solveEquation(equation)  
        FUNCTION parse_side(side)  
            SET tokens TO the result of replacing plus signs in side with delimiter plus sign and replacing minus signs in side with delimiter minus sign and splitting the resulting string by the delimiter  
            SET x_count TO zero  
            SET num_sum TO zero  
            FOR each token IN tokens

        SET mouse_start TO zero

                SET v TO i MULTIPLIED BY n PLUS j

                ELSE IF c EQUALS the character representing uppercase M  
                    SET mouse_start TO v  
                ELSE IF c EQUALS the character representing uppercase F  
                    SET food TO v

    FUNCTION minimumDifference(nums)  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF nums DIVIDED BY two  
        SET total_sum TO the SUM OF nums  
        SET target TO total_sum DIVIDED BY two  
        SET min_diff TO positive infinity  
        
        SET left_half TO the first n elements of nums

        SET left_sums TO a list containing empty dictionaries repeated n PLUS one times  
        SET right_sums TO a list containing empty dictionaries repeated n PLUS one times  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO n  
            FOR each combination of i elements IN left_half  
                SET subset_sum TO the SUM OF the current combination  
                IF subset_sum EXISTS AS A KEY IN left_sums at position i  
                    DO NOTHING  
                ELSE  
                    SET the value at key subset_sum IN left_sums at position i TO zero  
                END IF  
                INCREMENT the value at key subset_sum IN left_sums at position i BY one  
            END FOR  
            
            FOR each combination of i elements IN right_half  
                SET subset_sum TO the SUM OF the current combination  
                IF subset_sum EXISTS AS A KEY IN right_sums at position i  
                    DO NOTHING  
                ELSE  
                    SET the value at key subset_sum IN right_sums at position i TO zero  
                END IF  
                INCREMENT the value at key subset_sum IN right_sums at position i BY one  
            END FOR

            SET right_values TO the keys of right_sums at position n MINUS i SORTED in ascending order  
            
            SET j TO zero  
            SET k TO the LENGTH OF right_values MINUS one  
            
            WHILE j LESS THAN the LENGTH OF left_values AND k GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero

                ELSE IF current_sum GREATER THAN target  
                    DECREMENT k BY one  
                ELSE  
                    RETURN zero  
                END IF  
            END WHILE  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN min_diff  
    END FUNCTION

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION encode(s)  
        FUNCTION get_encoded_length(count, substring)  
            RETURN the LENGTH OF the string CONVERTED FROM count PLUS the LENGTH OF substring PLUS two  
        END FUNCTION  

        FUNCTION dp(i, j)  
            SET substring TO the element at position i UP TO and INCLUDING position j OF s  
            SET n TO j MINUS i PLUS one  
            IF n LESS THAN five THEN  
                RETURN substring  
            END IF  

            SET shortest TO substring  
            FOR k FROM one TO n DIVIDED BY two PLUS one  
                IF n MODULO k EQUALS zero THEN  
                    SET repeat_count TO n DIVIDED BY k  
                    IF substring EQUALS substring from position zero UP TO but NOT INCLUDING position k REPEATED repeat_count TIMES THEN  
                        SET encoded_candidate TO string CONVERTED FROM repeat_count CONCATENATED WITH the LEFT SQUARE BRACKET CONCATENATED WITH dp(i, i PLUS k MINUS one) CONCATENATED WITH the RIGHT SQUARE BRACKET  
                        IF the LENGTH OF encoded_candidate LESS THAN the LENGTH OF shortest THEN  
                            SET shortest TO encoded_candidate  
                        END IF  
                    END IF  
                END IF  
            END FOR  

            FOR k FROM i TO j MINUS one  
                SET left_encoded TO dp(i, k)  
                SET right_encoded TO dp(k PLUS one, j)  
                SET combined TO left_encoded CONCATENATED WITH right_encoded  
                IF the LENGTH OF combined LESS THAN the LENGTH OF shortest THEN  
                    SET shortest TO combined  
                END IF  
            END FOR  

            RETURN shortest  
        END FUNCTION  

        RETURN dp(zero, the LENGTH OF s MINUS one)  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS
